definitions.definition: Something homologous ; a homologous organ or part, chemical compound, chromosome, gene, or cultural element.

subdefinitions.definition: A phoneme , morpheme , or word shared by two languages or dialects , via cognation or naturalization .

One of a group of similar DNA sequences that share a common ancestry, or the peptides or proteins that they encode; the counterpart gene or protein in another taxon evolved from a common ancestor (molecularly it may be either identical or similar).
examples: TP53 is the human homolog of murine Trp53 .

subdefinitions.definition: A member of a homologous series .
A belief, practice, concept, or artifact that has a counterpart in another culture.

main_definition: Something homologous ; a homologous organ or part, chemical compound, chromosome, gene, or cultural element.
